==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pipe layer
<hw>Pipe" lay`er</hw></mhw>. <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who lays conducting
pipes in the ground, as for water, gas, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Polit. Cant)</fld> <def>A politician who works in
secret; -- in this sense, usually written as one word.</def>
<mark>[U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pipe laying</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Pipelaying</ent>⟦br⟧
